class pygcu.red.RedReturn[source]

Bases: object

Red logging utility class to capture output in Wherescape Red Example Usage:

1# import pygcu
2
3# Red = RedReturn()
4# Exit = Red.rreturn
5# Red.log("this is a log")
6# Red.info("this is some info")
7# Exit(LEVEL_SUCCESS, "done and return")

This following code will generate the following output as a string

1
(2) done and return
(0) this is a log
(1) this is some info

ws_parameter_read(parameter: str, refresh: bool = False) → RedParameter[source]

Reads a parameter from Wherescape Red.

THis function calls the built-in WsParameterRead sproc, and returns with both the name and description of the parameter. Function is case-sensitive and will return None, if not found

Parameters:

  • parameter (str) – The parameter to query

  • refresh (bool) – Refreshes cache of parameter value

ws_parameter_write(param: RedParameter) → RedParameter[source]

Writes a parameter to Wherescape Red.

This function simply wraps the execute statement, necessary to write a parameter in Wherescape Red, in textwrap dedent to remove whitespace in the execute statement.

Parameters:

  • parameter (str) – The parameter to write to.

  • value (str) – The value of the written parameter.

  • comment (str) – The comment field to write information about the value or parameter.
